Most mainstream Linux distributions are removing native 32-bit (x86_32) support
treating it as obsolete.
Major distros like Ubuntu, Fedora, and Fedora-based projects have either removed 32-bit installation images or proposed doing so.
Support is shifting toward 64-bit systems, with Firefox aiming to end 32-bit Linux support by 2026.

